Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.20,0:00:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Dr. David Hawkins. I've been a psychiatrist for the last 35 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.20,0:00:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,psychoanalyst, nutritionist, researcher into the relationship between nutrition and brain chemistry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.20,0:00:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The last 10 years I've been doing research on the nature of consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.20,0:00:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and its relationship to that which the world calls spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.55,0:00:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This involves the relationship between body, mind, and spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.55,0:00:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the relationship between body, mind, and spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.55,0:00:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And how does it relate to our topic for today, which is how to let go of depression?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.55,0:00:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Depression, despondency, that plague of mankind which has been there since ancient biblical days
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.55,0:00:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and which today is being called a minor epidemic.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.55,0:00:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,A minor epidemic with a rising suicide rate amongst young people, especially adolescents.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.55,0:00:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Very timely, very important in all of our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.55,0:00:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Few of us have managed to live on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.55,0:01:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,For any great length of time without experiencing depression.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.55,0:01:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe minor in the form of regrets, mourning, loss, loss of loved ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.55,0:01:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the loss of things that we have valued in our life because of their meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.74,0:01:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we're going into that today looking at it from the viewpoint of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.58,0:01:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but we'll also cover what is the place of biochemistry, what is the place of antidepressants.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.58,0:01:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Are these the cause or are these the effect of the depression?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.98,0:01:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In talking about this, we'll again have to review what is that relationship between body, mind, and spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.53,0:01:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,which we'll be talking about because we'll be talking about the treatment
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.53,0:01:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and the understanding of depression on all three levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.53,0:01:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So we need to review again, as we have in other talks in this series,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.42,0:01:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that the body has no way of experiencing itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.42,0:02:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The body cannot experience its own bodiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.68,0:02:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It cannot experience its own sensations.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.68,0:02:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The body is experienced in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.90,0:02:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Mind, curiously enough, also has no real capacity to experience itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.90,0:02:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Memories, thoughts, feelings, fantasies of the future, daydreams,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.90,0:02:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,all of these are registered and experienced in a field which is larger and more diffuse,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.90,0:02:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,a field of energy that we call consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.90,0:02:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A field that is currently being researched with advanced theoretical physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.90,0:02:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The relationship of mind to this great field called consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.90,0:02:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness itself, curiously, has to be experienced by something even greater
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.06,0:02:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and formless, and that we call awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.06,0:03:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So it is because of awareness that we're aware of what is going on within consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.06,0:03:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness allows us to know that which is going on in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.06,0:03:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Mind allows us to know that which is going on in our feelings, our emotions, our memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.32,0:03:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It allows us to know what the sensations are from the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.38,0:03:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,reporting to us our experience of the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.38,0:03:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, all of this is going on within consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.38,0:03:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this, as well as our other talks, we have emphasized the importance of addressing issues,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.38,0:03:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and addressing the highest level, the level where there is the most power,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.38,0:03:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,so that a change on the level of consciousness, a change within mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.38,0:03:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,brings about an alteration within the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.48,0:03:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,In talking about depression, that aspect of the part of the body we'll be interested in is the brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.48,0:03:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The brain and its hormones and its neurotransmitters,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.48,0:03:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and how depression affects the physiology of the brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.48,0:03:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the real causes of depression then?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.48,0:04:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,As we look into that, we will be looking at a map of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.96,0:04:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which we have been using in this series of talks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.96,0:04:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A mathematical model in which we have levels of consciousness in what we call the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.96,0:04:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The levels of consciousness starting from the lowest,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.96,0:04:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which we have calibrated at zero, death,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.96,0:04:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,all the way to the highest, calibrated at 600,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.96,0:04:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a very high, joyful state,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.96,0:04:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and one beyond which the world calls enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.96,0:04:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Within those levels, you will see that the energy fields have a direction,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.96,0:04:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,indicated by the arrows.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.96,0:04:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The indication of the arrows is whether we experience this as a positive asset in our life,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.96,0:04:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,or whether it has a negative deleterious effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.96,0:04:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And we notice that in about the middle of the box,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.15,0:04:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,at a level called courage, which is calibrated at an energy field of 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.15,0:04:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that these energies now,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.15,0:04:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly go neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.15,0:05:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And we notice that those energy fields above the level of courage,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.15,0:05:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,a level which we cross by telling the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.15,0:05:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,now the energy fields swing to the right and indicate a positive
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.15,0:05:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,or life-supportive energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.15,0:05:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,all the way up to love at 500 and joy at 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.15,0:05:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This will be important for us to refer to,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.98,0:05:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to have a context in which to hold our subject for today,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.98,0:05:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because we are going to be talking about the bottom of the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.98,0:05:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We are going to be talking about those human experiences,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.98,0:05:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,starting at the bottom called guilt, apathy, grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.98,0:05:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,These energy fields expressing themselves in an emotion,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.98,0:05:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,self-hatred, self-recrimination, hopelessness, despair, despondency,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.98,0:05:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,all these accompanied by feelings of regret, loss and despondency.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.62,0:05:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In these energy fields of depression then,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.62,0:06:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,our view of the world, our view of the world is that it is a sad
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.62,0:06:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and hopeless place of sin and suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.62,0:06:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Our view of God then, the God of a world like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.82,0:06:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,would be one who is unfeeling, uncaring,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.82,0:06:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,from whom you are separated, who ignores you,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.82,0:06:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,or possibly is dead, or at its worst, if he is alive,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.82,0:06:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,would perhaps be the destroyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.82,0:06:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of your guiltiness, worthlessness, sinfulness,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.82,0:06:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,a God like that would throw you into hell,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.82,0:06:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,absolute destruction forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.82,0:06:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,When we look over at the process going on in consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.07,0:06:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in these lower energy fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.07,0:06:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,we see coming out of deflated, the one right above it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.07,0:06:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,we come into one called dispirited,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.07,0:06:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the loss of that energy of life, the desire to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.07,0:06:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming lower to this apathy state,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.07,0:06:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,we see that the process going on in consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.07,0:06:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is the loss of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.07,0:07:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the loss of the life energy within,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.07,0:07:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,which comes within the being,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.07,0:07:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,it no longer attracts energy from the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.07,0:07:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and so our process is one of being de-energized,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.07,0:07:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,leading to the self-hatred of destruction
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.07,0:07:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and these states preceding death,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.07,0:07:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,so that out of this we often see a pattern of passive suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.07,0:07:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So today we'll be looking at
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.07,0:07:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,active suicide and passive suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.07,0:07:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What do they come out of?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.07,0:07:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,How can they be handled?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.07,0:07:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What do they really mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.07,0:07:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In what way can we create an understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.07,0:07:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of this whole field of depression,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.07,0:07:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,this plague of mankind?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.07,0:07:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we benefit from an understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.30,0:07:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of the study of the nature of consciousness itself?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.87,0:07:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We notice that all these energy fields below the level of courage
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.87,0:07:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,have a direction,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.87,0:07:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and a negative direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.87,0:08:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And seldom do one of these emotions come through
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.87,0:08:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,all by themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.87,0:08:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Generally, one negative emotion tends to pull
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.87,0:08:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,all of them to some degree,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.94,0:08:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,so that in depression then,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.94,0:08:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,there is also feelings coming from this level
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.94,0:08:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of self-blame, self-hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.94,0:08:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There's feelings coming from this level
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.94,0:08:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of hopelessness and despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.94,0:08:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There's regrets about the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.94,0:08:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and fears about the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.94,0:08:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Very often there is anger,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.29,0:08:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and we often hear it said
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.29,0:08:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that depression is anger turned inward.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.67,0:08:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So one way that's recommended in traditional psychotherapy
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.67,0:08:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is to try to energize and bring up the anger
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.67,0:08:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,which is accompanying the depression.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.67,0:08:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But then we have to ask,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.80,0:08:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,so then what is the source of the anger?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.80,0:08:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And we will find out that both the anger and the depression
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.80,0:08:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,are coming from the same error.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.80,0:08:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,From having made the same mistake
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.80,0:09:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,within the mind, within consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.99,0:09:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And what is that error which we're going to find,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.99,0:09:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,whether we look at the anger,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.99,0:09:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,we look at the fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.99,0:09:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,we look at the grief, the apathy, the guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.99,0:09:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll find that for some reason
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.99,0:09:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the person has placed their survival
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.99,0:09:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,on something outside of themself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.99,0:09:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that all these energy fuels here,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.99,0:09:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,which are in this direction,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.02,0:09:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,are based on placing the source of your happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.02,0:09:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,as something outside of oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.02,0:09:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes from having been vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.02,0:09:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes from being the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.02,0:09:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Being the victim, being at the effect of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.09,0:09:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,a cause that we see as being outside
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.57,0:09:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of our own consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.57,0:09:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We put the source of our happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.57,0:09:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,somehow out into the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.57,0:09:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that vulnerability to depression
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.57,0:09:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is there, and so long as we
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.57,0:09:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,put the source of our happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.57,0:10:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,as something outside of ourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.57,0:10:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That common frailty of human consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.34,0:10:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to say that, well, when I get that degree,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.34,0:10:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,then I'll be successful and happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.34,0:10:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,When I learn that foreign language,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.46,0:10:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,when I get to move into that apartment,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.46,0:10:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,when I get that fur coat,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.46,0:10:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,when I get that new car,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.46,0:10:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,when I get that PhD,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.46,0:10:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,when I get my medical license,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.46,0:10:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,if I can only get that internship,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.46,0:10:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,if I could get that relationship,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.46,0:10:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,if I could just change that person out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.46,0:10:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,if I could get my aunt to stop drinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.46,0:10:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,if our company would only come out of the red
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.46,0:10:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and go into the black,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.46,0:10:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it is always out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.46,0:10:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Placing the source of one's happiness then
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.46,0:10:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,outside of oneself is putting oneself
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.46,0:10:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in the vulnerable position to depression,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.46,0:10:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,anxiety, fear, and a potential loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.46,0:10:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only by owning ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.14,0:11:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,as the source of our happiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.14,0:11:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience of our own existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.14,0:11:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,independent and beyond that which happens
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.14,0:11:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,within the world that we become immune
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.14,0:11:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to depressive episodes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.14,0:11:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And so to understand that,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.49,0:11:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll have to review briefly
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.49,0:11:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,this map of consciousness again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.49,0:11:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of you who have seen the other talks,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.49,0:11:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,each time that we look at it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.49,0:11:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to be looking at it from a different angle
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.49,0:11:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,with a different emphasis.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.49,0:11:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And each time we look at it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.49,0:11:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,it alters our own understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.49,0:11:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,of the nature of human consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.49,0:11:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And so it's never the same every time we look at it
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.49,0:11:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're coming at it from a different context
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.49,0:11:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,now with a broader understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.49,0:11:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we look at it again and we'll see,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.29,0:11:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,as we said before, that these energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.29,0:11:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,are calibrated as to their energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.29,0:11:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the relative energy and power of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.29,0:11:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That they have either a negative direction
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.29,0:11:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,or a positive direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.29,0:11:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And that there's a crucial crossover
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.29,0:11:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,in the middle at the level of courage,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.29,0:12:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,which we said is crossed over by the telling of the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.29,0:12:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, the telling of the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.42,0:12:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is that my happiness does not depend
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.42,0:12:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,on anything outside of myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.42,0:12:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself, by my own inner decision,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.42,0:12:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,by my own integrity, by my intentions,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.42,0:12:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,by the way I see myself and my relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.42,0:12:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to the events of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.42,0:12:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,am the source of my own happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.42,0:12:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And so at the bottom we have maximum victimhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.80,0:12:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In which the total source of one's happiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.96,0:12:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the total source of one's happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.96,0:12:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,has been placed outside of oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.96,0:12:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The loss of that brings about self-contempt,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.96,0:12:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,self-hatred, there is nothing within the self now to love
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.96,0:12:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because that which was loved
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.96,0:12:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,was seen as something outside of oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.96,0:12:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The stage above that with an energy field of apathy,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.41,0:12:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,which we know as hopelessness and despair,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.41,0:12:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is a state of no energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.41,0:12:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So that a person in that state,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.41,0:13:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,we would say, is in a severe clinical depression.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.41,0:13:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The person is usually unresponsive.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.41,0:13:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They sit in the chair and stare blankly out the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.41,0:13:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,very often unresponsive,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.41,0:13:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,into any communication, unable to talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.41,0:13:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,very often stop eating,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.41,0:13:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,may not be able to sleep,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.41,0:13:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,unable to function in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.63,0:13:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are the severe depressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.63,0:13:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And these people, of course, are seeing their life as sad,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.63,0:13:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,they see the future as hopeless,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.63,0:13:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,they see themselves as empty and worthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.63,0:13:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Their conception of God, as we've mentioned before,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.63,0:13:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the God of that kind of a world
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.63,0:13:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is a God who ignores you and doesn't care for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.63,0:13:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's a state of total unlovingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.63,0:13:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling unloved.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.40,0:13:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Our clinical experience indicates that these lower three states,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.40,0:13:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,which collectively we call despondency and depression,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.40,0:13:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,come out of the failure
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.40,0:13:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to have handled the energy field above it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.40,0:14:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,which we call fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.40,0:14:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The facing of the underlying fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.26,0:14:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the depression is coming about
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.26,0:14:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,from the loss of meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.26,0:14:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So it isn't the things outside of ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.26,0:14:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that we've placed our happiness on,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.26,0:14:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that is the difficulty,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.26,0:14:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the meaning that we have attached to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.26,0:14:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't the PhD degree,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.26,0:14:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the meaning of that PhD degree.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.26,0:14:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't that relationship,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.26,0:14:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the meaning of that relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.26,0:14:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't that position or title as president of the company,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.26,0:14:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,or financial success,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.26,0:14:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,or having the right address.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.26,0:14:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the meaning,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.74,0:14:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the way in which we held those things,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.74,0:14:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,their importance and their value.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.74,0:14:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What we projected onto that,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.80,0:14:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the way we hold it now then,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.80,0:14:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,depends on the meaning that we have given it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.80,0:14:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In and of itself, it has no meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.80,0:14:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In and of itself, it merely is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.80,0:14:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So meaning is a construction.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.80,0:14:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A mental construction
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.80,0:15:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have projected out onto
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.80,0:15:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,by giving a thing value.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.80,0:15:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The value then is coming out of our own consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.80,0:15:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,projected onto something that we are seeing
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.80,0:15:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,as outside of ourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.80,0:15:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing oneself as separated
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.96,0:15:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,from the source of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.96,0:15:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There is myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.96,0:15:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and then there is that outside myself
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.96,0:15:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,from which I feel separated.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.96,0:15:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the fantasy that if I could reunite with that,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.96,0:15:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,have that, control it,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.96,0:15:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,then that would heal
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.96,0:15:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the inner feeling of lack and separation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.96,0:15:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,To feel separated from that which one wants
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.96,0:15:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is to feel separated from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.96,0:15:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So that over here the view of God then
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.96,0:15:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in these depressed states
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.96,0:15:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you are totally separated
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.96,0:15:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,from the source of your happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.96,0:15:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,As we move out of depression into fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.41,0:15:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the way to get out of the depression then
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.41,0:15:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is to look at the underlying fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.41,0:15:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the fear?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.50,0:16:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take the woman rocking back and forth
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.50,0:16:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in her chair staring out the window
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.50,0:16:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,who got the telegram from the State Department
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.50,0:16:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that her son was killed in action.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.63,0:16:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And we said in another talk on this subject,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.63,0:16:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is actually clinically
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.63,0:16:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,an example of what actually happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.63,0:16:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is within several weeks she got a telegram
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.63,0:16:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,from the State Department stating that it was a mistake
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.63,0:16:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and that the serial number was off by one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.63,0:16:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And curiously enough the name had been the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.63,0:16:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they corrected the error
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.63,0:16:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and the State Department regretted
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.63,0:16:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the previous telegram.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.63,0:16:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So when the family told her this,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.63,0:16:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,she just kept on rocking back and forth
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.63,0:16:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and staring out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.76,0:16:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother, mother, they all shook her and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.76,0:16:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't you hear? Joey is not dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.76,0:16:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He's alive. He's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.76,0:16:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He's in an R&R camp in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.76,0:16:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And she kept on rocking back and forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.76,0:16:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So that something had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.76,0:16:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, something had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.76,0:16:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy field then, the state,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.89,0:17:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,she had obviously been holding her son
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.89,0:17:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and her relationship to her son
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.89,0:17:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,as a source, a major source of happiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.89,0:17:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,being a widow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.89,0:17:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That relationship was prime in her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.89,0:17:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Now something had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.02,0:17:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy of the field had now brought about
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.02,0:17:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,a change in the brain chemistry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.02,0:17:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we see that the shift in brain chemistry now
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.02,0:17:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is a consequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.02,0:17:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It was due to the loss of the meaning in her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.02,0:17:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This energy field then expresses itself
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.66,0:17:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,on the level of brain chemistry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.66,0:17:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We said all things are physical,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.66,0:17:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,mental, and spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.66,0:17:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritually, the meaning here,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.66,0:17:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the separation from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.66,0:17:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotionally, the significance of this relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.66,0:17:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And now on the physical level,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.66,0:17:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,in the brain chemistry,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.66,0:17:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,there was a shift.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.66,0:17:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a loss of neurotransmitters.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.66,0:17:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see in the brain then,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.66,0:17:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,in a depressive condition,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.66,0:17:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,a depression of essential neurotransmitters,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.66,0:17:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,in certain areas of the brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.66,0:18:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And this accompanies the depression.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.66,0:18:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's possible then to ameliorate
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.66,0:18:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the expression of this symptom
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.66,0:18:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,on the physical level
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.66,0:18:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,by the use of antidepressants.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.66,0:18:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And in treating all these conditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.66,0:18:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we find it most efficacious to treat them
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.66,0:18:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,all levels simultaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.66,0:18:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,To address the person in a dialogue
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.66,0:18:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,where they begin to examine
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.66,0:18:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,how they have placed meaning and significance
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.66,0:18:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,fill the emptiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.66,0:18:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,internal emptiness of their life
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.66,0:18:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,with things from the outside
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.66,0:18:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to give it meaning and significance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.66,0:18:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Thereby creating this vulnerability.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.69,0:18:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The way it's held psychologically.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.69,0:18:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And at the same time to treat it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.69,0:18:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,on the physical level.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.69,0:18:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So the antidepressants nowadays
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.69,0:18:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,are very effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.69,0:18:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The side effects are easy to watch for and control.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.69,0:18:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Generally it is a very safe thing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.69,0:18:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to treat pharmacologically.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.69,0:18:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And the antidepressants are very effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.69,0:18:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Often used in combinations
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.69,0:18:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps with some other drugs such as lithium.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.69,0:18:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They're extremely effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.69,0:19:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They take the person out of the bottom of the box
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.69,0:19:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and lift them up to a higher state.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.69,0:19:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So that in a higher state
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.69,0:19:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,they're then able to respond to psychotherapy
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.69,0:19:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,or spiritual counseling
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.69,0:19:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to try and alleviate the conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.69,0:19:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that brought about this vulnerability.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.69,0:19:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Facing the fear then,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.17,0:19:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,facing the fear
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.17,0:19:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that underlies the depression,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.17,0:19:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,relieves the depression.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.17,0:19:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And what is the fear?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.17,0:19:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The fear is I have lost the meaning of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.17,0:19:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I have lost that which is of value.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.30,0:19:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And it will never be replaced.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.30,0:19:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,See depression, hopelessness
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.30,0:19:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,means that the expectation of the future is zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.30,0:19:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no hope that meaning and significance
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.30,0:19:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that a context will be recreated
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.30,0:19:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that will re-energize
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.30,0:19:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and give one's life meaning again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.55,0:19:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This of course is an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.55,0:19:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But at the time the hopelessness
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.55,0:19:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is based on this perspective,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.55,0:19:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,this perception of one's self
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.55,0:20:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and one's relationship to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.55,0:20:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to face the fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.55,0:20:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we have a depressed person
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.55,0:20:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we look to see what is the loss here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.55,0:20:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The loss of the job,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.55,0:20:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the loss of vitality,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.55,0:20:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the loss of youth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.55,0:20:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,People become depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.55,0:20:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Middle age, the loss of opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.55,0:20:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They see middle age as
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.55,0:20:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,life having passed them by
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.55,0:20:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and now they've lost their opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.55,0:20:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The loss of looks to a person
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.55,0:20:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in whom their looks
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.55,0:20:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,has been very important in their life
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.55,0:20:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and their way of relating
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.55,0:20:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and their sense of self-value.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.55,0:20:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The middle-aged woman
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.55,0:20:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,who feels she is losing her looks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.55,0:20:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And if she is based on her power in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.55,0:20:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and valued that greatly,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.55,0:20:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,then the loss of the looks to her
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.55,0:20:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is a great danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.55,0:20:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And not just a superficial thing
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.55,0:20:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,such as vanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.55,0:20:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's far more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.55,0:20:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's her whole sense of self-worth and value.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.55,0:20:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Beauty to her has become
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.55,0:20:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is valuable
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.55,0:20:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and makes her a worthwhile person.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.55,0:20:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So we look to see
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.55,0:20:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the underlying fear
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.55,0:20:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and we get the person
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.55,0:21:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to be willing to look at this fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.55,0:21:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of depression,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.00,0:21:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,now what the person has to handle is fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.00,0:21:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Because fear has to do with the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.00,0:21:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How am I going to live
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.00,0:21:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,without this which has given my life significance?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.00,0:21:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We see this in the addictions, for instance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.00,0:21:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You might say
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.00,0:21:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that anybody who gets depressed
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.00,0:21:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,has been addicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.00,0:21:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Addicted to what?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.00,0:21:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Addicted to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.00,0:21:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,placing their survival
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.13,0:21:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,on something outside of themself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.13,0:21:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In the addiction,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.13,0:21:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,if we threaten to take away
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.13,0:21:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is outside of themself,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.13,0:21:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the person has been placing their survival
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.13,0:21:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,on happiness, in this case the drug,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.13,0:21:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,we see terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.13,0:21:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only fear, but absolute terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.13,0:21:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The conviction within
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.13,0:21:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that it will be impossible to live in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.13,0:21:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,without access to that substance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.13,0:21:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we have the person look at the fear
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.13,0:21:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and then utilize the time
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.13,0:21:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and the techniques, clinically,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.13,0:21:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have found handle fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.29,0:21:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to be with the fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.29,0:21:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop labeling it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.32,0:22:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop the thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.32,0:22:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus instead on the exact experience
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.32,0:22:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of what is coming up
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.32,0:22:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,as one looks at
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.32,0:22:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is feared within mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.32,0:22:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,To look at that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.32,0:22:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and then to go into the radical truth
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.32,0:22:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of what is literally being experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.32,0:22:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,within oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.32,0:22:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And the willingness to surrender to that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.32,0:22:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and to let go resisting the fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.80,0:22:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,As this happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.80,0:22:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the sensations run through the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.80,0:22:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I say to the person,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.80,0:22:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,what are you experiencing in your body?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.80,0:22:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,My mouth is so dry I can hardly talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.80,0:22:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,My heart feels like it's fluttering.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.80,0:22:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,My stomach feels like it's turning over.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.80,0:22:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel cramps in my abdomen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.80,0:22:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,My knees are so weak I can hardly stand up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.06,0:22:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we start with them one by one.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.06,0:22:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We say, all right,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.06,0:22:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the tingling in your legs and your knees,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.06,0:22:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,could you let go resisting that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.06,0:22:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you just let yourself experience that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.06,0:22:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and be with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.06,0:22:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you feeling here?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.06,0:22:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Just sense what you're sensing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.06,0:22:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you sensing?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.06,0:23:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm sensing a tingling in my legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.06,0:23:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say, can you handle a tingling in your legs?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.06,0:23:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You've handled headaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.66,0:23:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You've handled major surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.66,0:23:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You've handled deaths in the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.66,0:23:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm certain you can handle a tingling in your legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.66,0:23:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And the person will say, yes, I can handle that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.66,0:23:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, okay, let go resisting the tingling in the legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.73,0:23:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how about the cramps in the abdomen?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.73,0:23:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you let go resisting that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.73,0:23:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.73,0:23:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you stop calling them cramps?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.73,0:23:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you let go resisting that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.73,0:23:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.95,0:23:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go up higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.95,0:23:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the flip-flops in the stomach?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.95,0:23:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you handle that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.95,0:23:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I can handle that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.95,0:23:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you just handle the experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.95,0:23:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,stop calling it flip-flops in your stomach?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.95,0:23:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,How about the beating of your pulse?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.95,0:23:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you let go wanting to resist that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.95,0:23:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Just let your pulse beat away if it wants to.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.95,0:23:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,How about the dry mouth?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.95,0:23:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we get the person to realize,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.95,0:23:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, I can handle that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.95,0:23:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And we agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.95,0:23:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody can handle fearful thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.95,0:23:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no such thing as handling fearful thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.66,0:23:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Fearful thoughts create themselves by the thousands.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.66,0:24:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you handle one whole bank of fearful thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.66,0:24:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,a whole new bank will arise.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.66,0:24:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be late for the plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.66,0:24:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't get on the plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.66,0:24:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be afraid of the plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.66,0:24:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Something's going to happen on the plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.66,0:24:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I might go to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.66,0:24:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the mind will just create an endless series of fears.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.66,0:24:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What it can handle is a dry mouth,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.66,0:24:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,tingling in the legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.66,0:24:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And the only thing a person benefits
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.66,0:24:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,is relief of depression.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.66,0:24:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, oh, I see I'm not depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.66,0:24:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I see I was terrified of the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.66,0:24:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that I will never find happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.66,0:24:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,without that which I wished,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.66,0:24:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,longed for, desired.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.66,0:24:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was convinced that I had to have that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.66,0:24:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to survive and be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.62,0:24:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, when you talk to people
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.62,0:24:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,who were convinced of that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.62,0:24:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and were on sizable doses of drugs,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.62,0:24:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, they were really as close to actually
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.62,0:24:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,needing something to survive
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.65,0:24:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,as anybody could be on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.65,0:24:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,When they faced the fear of it all,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.65,0:24:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,they found that life was joyful.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.65,0:24:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Life was complete. Life was full.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.65,0:24:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They enjoyed life for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.65,0:25:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So we know it's based on an illusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.65,0:25:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore we have the courage
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.65,0:25:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,for the patient to take them with us
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.65,0:25:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to look at the fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.65,0:25:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,like we take the child by the hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.65,0:25:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was a kid, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.65,0:25:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody on the block told me about boogeymen.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.65,0:25:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And so my mother had ridiculed
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.65,0:25:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,boogeymen and ghosts and things like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.65,0:25:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,but somehow this kid's convincing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.65,0:25:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, he was five years older than I was,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.65,0:25:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,so he knew what he was talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.65,0:25:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So what my mother did is take me by the hand
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.65,0:25:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and we went down to the dark basement
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.65,0:25:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,with flashlights and we looked all over for boogeymen.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.65,0:25:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So to have someone with you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.65,0:25:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to look at this fear then is helpful
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.65,0:25:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,because our child is frightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.65,0:25:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Our child doesn't understand
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.65,0:25:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the nature of real life in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.65,0:25:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the child comes up and says,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.65,0:25:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,gee, without that I won't be able to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.65,0:25:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And very often it has been
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.65,0:25:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,a parent substitute,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.65,0:25:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,which was envisioned as being out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.65,0:25:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What about animals?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.97,0:25:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't understand anger
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.97,0:25:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because it said, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.97,0:25:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,as we said before, that depression
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.06,0:25:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is anger turned within.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.06,0:26:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the basis of the anger then?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.16,0:26:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take somebody who is really
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.16,0:26:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,into survival on something outside of themself.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.16,0:26:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, we'll use the attic, let's say.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.16,0:26:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And you threaten to take away his bottle
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.16,0:26:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,or his supplier, flush his drugs down the toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.16,0:26:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And he goes into a rage.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.16,0:26:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's very clear to us
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.16,0:26:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,what the source of the anger is, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.16,0:26:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of the anger
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.16,0:26:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is exactly the same fantasy,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.16,0:26:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that the source of happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.16,0:26:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is something outside of myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.16,0:26:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I have placed it on some object,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.16,0:26:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,some person, place, or thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.16,0:26:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The place,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.42,0:26:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of your happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.42,0:26:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,on something outside of yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.42,0:26:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,puts you in a negative energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.42,0:26:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,because basically it is a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.42,0:26:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of your happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.42,0:26:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is not something outside of yourself at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.42,0:26:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only when we own
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.61,0:26:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that we are the source of our happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.61,0:26:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that the energy field goes
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.61,0:26:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in a positive direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.61,0:26:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can move the person then
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.61,0:26:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,out of depression and despondency,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.61,0:26:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,get them to face the fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.61,0:26:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,get them to desire something better
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.61,0:27:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,for themself,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.61,0:27:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,turn that anger into the anger
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.61,0:27:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,at being victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.64,0:27:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The anger instead of at the loss of the object.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.64,0:27:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the endless rationalizations
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.64,0:27:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and explanations
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.64,0:27:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to try and make this anger sound justified.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.64,0:27:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They promised me this,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.64,0:27:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,they signed a contract,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.64,0:27:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,they sent a check
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.64,0:27:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to make it sound good.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.74,0:27:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of that is always outside of ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.74,0:27:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and the explanations,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.74,0:27:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the details,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.74,0:27:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the events are only justifications
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.74,0:27:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,for this anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.02,0:27:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we use this anger now
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.02,0:27:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,instead we turn it at anger
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.02,0:27:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,at the vulnerability.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.02,0:27:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, now it's time to be angry
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.02,0:27:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,at what the real cause was
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.02,0:27:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and the real cause was
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.02,0:27:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I was brought up in a world
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.02,0:27:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,which taught me to think this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.02,0:27:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I was taught that this is the right way to think.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.02,0:27:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the way to be angry at.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.02,0:27:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That we were taught how to think
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.02,0:27:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in a way that set us up
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.02,0:27:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,as potential victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.02,0:28:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.02,0:28:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The great American way is success.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.02,0:28:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.02,0:28:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Will success bring us happiness?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.02,0:28:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Where I used to live in the East
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.02,0:28:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,was a whole row of millionaires
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.02,0:28:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and they routinely committed suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.02,0:28:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and took overdoses
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.02,0:28:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and they were not at all immune
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.02,0:28:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to the human vulnerabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.02,0:28:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So worldly success,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.02,0:28:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,what we need to be angry at
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.02,0:28:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is what got us to sell ourselves out
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.02,0:28:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and how did we sell ourselves out
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.02,0:28:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and then to take pride in the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.02,0:28:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that we are willing to look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.02,0:28:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Move up to the courage
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.02,0:28:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to tell the truth about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.02,0:28:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.02,0:28:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,something within our consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.02,0:28:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,set us up to be vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.15,0:28:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.15,0:28:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And so if I start to take responsibility now
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.15,0:28:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and I say,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.15,0:28:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the way I was looking at this
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.15,0:28:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,set me up for this depression.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.34,0:28:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Set me up for this frustration and anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.34,0:28:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Set me up for this let down.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.34,0:28:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Set me up for this disappointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.73,0:29:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The courage then to look at that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.73,0:29:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and be willing to tell the truth about it
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.73,0:29:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,now changes the way I feel
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.73,0:29:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,about the whole subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.73,0:29:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can now move up to a situation
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.73,0:29:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,where I say to myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.73,0:29:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,well, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.73,0:29:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.18,0:29:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how people are taught in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.18,0:29:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and I grew up in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.18,0:29:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and I guess I learned the same as everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.18,0:29:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm willing to look at it
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.24,0:29:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in a different way
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.24,0:29:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and so we move up to willingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.24,0:29:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to look at it
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.24,0:29:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, yes, I agree to look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.24,0:29:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,My intention is up
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.24,0:29:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and I see at least the subject
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.24,0:29:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is promising and hopeful.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.24,0:29:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of a friendly world
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.30,0:29:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is promising and hopeful.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.30,0:29:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, there's going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.30,0:29:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,some benefit to me
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.30,0:29:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,not only in this particular situation
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.30,0:29:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but there's going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.30,0:29:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,a benefit to me as a human being
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.30,0:29:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that will last my lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.30,0:29:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because if I solve this one
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.30,0:29:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I've solved it for all time within myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.82,0:29:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to look at that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.82,0:30:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and the willingness to accept
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.82,0:30:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,what I find out
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.82,0:30:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,gives me a certain confidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.82,0:30:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,A certain confidence that there is a process
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.82,0:30:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,going on within me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.82,0:30:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That this depression has arisen
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.82,0:30:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to bring something to my attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.82,0:30:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as though it's saying
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.82,0:30:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,something is out, something is wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.82,0:30:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,within my mind, within my consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.82,0:30:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,within my spiritual position.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.82,0:30:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what pain means, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.82,0:30:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Pain means, please look at me,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.82,0:30:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,something is out.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.36,0:30:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Pharmacologically we can treat the depression,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.36,0:30:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of course, we can get the person
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.36,0:30:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,out of it temporarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.36,0:30:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But the person and his way of being in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.36,0:30:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and the way he's holding who he is
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.36,0:30:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and how he relates to the world
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.36,0:30:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and his universe and his expectations
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.36,0:30:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is not changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.36,0:30:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So the vulnerability remains the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.36,0:30:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And we know that people who are treated
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.36,0:30:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,with just antidepressants
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.36,0:30:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,will recover from this episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.36,0:30:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.36,0:30:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the whole context has not changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.36,0:30:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Without an understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.36,0:31:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and depth into the nature of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.36,0:31:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.49,0:31:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the vulnerability remains.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.49,0:31:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the person is subject
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.49,0:31:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to repeated bouts of depression
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.49,0:31:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,within their lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.90,0:31:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In looking at this in a holistic way
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.90,0:31:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,from the viewpoint of body, mind and spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.90,0:31:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to address what is the basic cause
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.90,0:31:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,so as to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.90,0:31:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,bring about an immunity
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.90,0:31:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,from further episodes
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.90,0:31:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of this debilitating experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.19,0:31:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The acceptance then,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.19,0:31:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,moving into accepting
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.19,0:31:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the setup
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.19,0:31:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and seeing what the setup is
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.19,0:31:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,without blaming oneself,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.19,0:31:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,without getting into a make wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.19,0:31:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing wrong with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.19,0:31:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just that it doesn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.19,0:31:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been trained in our world
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.19,0:31:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to think that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.19,0:31:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all set up to think that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.19,0:31:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Our parents were set up to think that way
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.19,0:31:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore they set us up.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.19,0:31:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They just passed it on down.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.19,0:31:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,There are several times
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.19,0:31:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,when there's descriptions
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.19,0:31:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of very severe depressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.19,0:32:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So it belongs sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.19,0:32:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in the collective consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.19,0:32:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and we all got brainwashed
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.19,0:32:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,with the same programs
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.19,0:32:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that somehow happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.29,0:32:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and the source of it
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.29,0:32:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,is outside oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.29,0:32:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You see as we move up here,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.29,0:32:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to tell the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.29,0:32:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to look at this,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.29,0:32:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we see the energy fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.29,0:32:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the numbers, the power of the field
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.29,0:32:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,numbers jump like this
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.29,0:32:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and why is the energy field positive
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.29,0:32:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of negative?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.29,0:32:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because above the level of courage
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.29,0:32:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the person has stopped projecting
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.29,0:32:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of their happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.29,0:32:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,outside of themself.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.29,0:32:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The person has begun to re-own
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.29,0:32:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,their own power.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.29,0:32:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that the level of courage,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.29,0:32:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to tell the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.29,0:32:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to face with the situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.29,0:32:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,cope with it and handle it,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.29,0:32:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we see the process going on
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.29,0:32:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,within their power.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.29,0:32:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And by the time we move up
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.29,0:32:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to this energy level of acceptance
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.29,0:32:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,which we see they're a person
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.29,0:33:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that's confident and easy-going,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.29,0:33:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the confidence
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.29,0:33:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and easy-goingness coming from?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.29,0:33:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's coming from the awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.29,0:33:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that I am the source of my happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.29,0:33:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It means that person
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.29,0:33:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,has realized by now
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.29,0:33:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,in their emotional and psychological
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.29,0:33:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and spiritual growth
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.29,0:33:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that they are the cause
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.29,0:33:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of the happiness in their life.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.29,0:33:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a person on a desert island
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.29,0:33:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,somewhere in the South Pacific
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.29,0:33:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and sail away.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.29,0:33:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And you come back a year later
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.29,0:33:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll have a coconut factory
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.29,0:33:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and they'll be making flutes out of bamboo
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.29,0:33:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and the children will be learning songs
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.29,0:33:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and be teaching French to the natives.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.29,0:33:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll find a native girl
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.29,0:33:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and build a tree house within the tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.29,0:33:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Recreated now for himself
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.29,0:33:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the world around him as an expression
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.42,0:33:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that we are the source of our own happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.42,0:33:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The anger now,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.42,0:33:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the anger was based on
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.42,0:33:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,a deeper level
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.42,0:33:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is the anger at having sold ourselves out,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.42,0:33:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,having been sold out,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.42,0:33:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,by having been given this program
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.42,0:34:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to operate by
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.42,0:34:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and then find that it doesn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.61,0:34:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Our accepting that it doesn't work,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.61,0:34:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,our willingness to look at that
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.61,0:34:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and our willingness to change
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.67,0:34:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, okay,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.67,0:34:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,because how long does it take
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.67,0:34:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to find a position from which it will work?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.67,0:34:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It only really takes a matter of seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.67,0:34:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,How long does it take to come out of depression?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.67,0:34:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It only takes as long as
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.67,0:34:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it takes for one to become willing
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.67,0:34:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to look at the truth of what's happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.67,0:34:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.70,0:34:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The acceptance that that is what has happened
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.70,0:34:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and the realization
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.70,0:34:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that I am the source of my own happiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.70,0:34:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that that capacity is within me
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.70,0:34:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and my unwillingness
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.70,0:34:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to give it out to the world anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.70,0:34:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The reowning of that power
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.80,0:34:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and suddenly you feel
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.80,0:34:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,a state of lovingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.80,0:34:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly it doesn't matter
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.80,0:34:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.80,0:34:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The realization of that truth
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.80,0:34:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,allows you to experience yourself now
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.80,0:34:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in a far more whole
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.80,0:34:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and complete way.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.15,0:35:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Not from that lackingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.15,0:35:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,not from that vulnerability.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.15,0:35:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Just this realization
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.15,0:35:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that I am the source,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.15,0:35:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I have the power to create.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.15,0:35:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It is myself that projected
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.15,0:35:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the meaning onto this.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.15,0:35:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.28,0:35:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,they say one man's meat
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.28,0:35:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is another man's poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.28,0:35:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The same event
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.28,0:35:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,which would make one person happy
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.28,0:35:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is another person happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.28,0:35:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I have watched people resist
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.28,0:35:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,coming into money for instance
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.28,0:35:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was not within their value system.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.28,0:35:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not what they valued.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.79,0:35:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What they valued at the time
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.79,0:35:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,was not having money
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.79,0:35:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.79,0:35:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you were just giving them a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.79,0:35:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Winning the lottery
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.79,0:35:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,might make one person joyful
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.79,0:35:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and fill the other one with guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.79,0:35:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.08,0:35:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The difference is meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.08,0:35:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Who creates the meaning?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.08,0:35:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Who gave this something
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.08,0:35:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,outside of oneself
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.08,0:35:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the power and the significance?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.08,0:36:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the creator of the meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.08,0:36:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the one who chooses
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.08,0:36:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,what meaning to give.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.08,0:36:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore I have to look at
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.08,0:36:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the way in which I have
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.08,0:36:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,bought into social consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.08,0:36:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the values that I have
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.08,0:36:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,unwittingly allowed myself
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.08,0:36:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to be programmed by
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.08,0:36:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and say to myself
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.08,0:36:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,do I agree with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.08,0:36:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I willing to give it that same value?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.08,0:36:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The realization now
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.08,0:36:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that I have the power
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.08,0:36:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to resource myself
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.08,0:36:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to recontextualize my life
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.08,0:36:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to see how I have been doing this
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.08,0:36:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,it brings me a state of inner joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.08,0:36:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The realization that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.08,0:36:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I, I alone have the choice now.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.08,0:36:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I have the power.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.08,0:36:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the one that sets up the meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.08,0:36:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and gives these things
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.08,0:36:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the power over me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.08,0:36:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore it is really possible
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.08,0:36:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to come out of disappointment
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.08,0:36:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and grief and sadness
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.11,0:36:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and anger about the event
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.11,0:36:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,or even indifference
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.11,0:36:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to become willing
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.11,0:37:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to really look into it
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.11,0:37:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and re-experience my own inner self.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.11,0:37:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually a depressive episode
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.11,0:37:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,even a brief one
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.11,0:37:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,has within it then
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.11,0:37:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,actually the potential for joy
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.11,0:37:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,because it is something
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.11,0:37:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,coming up in our life saying
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.11,0:37:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,look at me, look at me, look at me
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.11,0:37:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,here is a mistake that has been causing you
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.11,0:37:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,pain and suffering for endless amounts of time
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.11,0:37:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and which will continue to cause you pain
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.11,0:37:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and suffering for endless amounts of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.11,0:37:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that inner state
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.21,0:37:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of inner joy and serenity
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.21,0:37:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,really comes about from a knowingness
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.21,0:37:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of one's own invulnerability
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.21,0:37:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore even though the depression
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.30,0:37:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is not currently clinically there
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.30,0:37:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the knowledge that one is vulnerable
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.30,0:37:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,precludes
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.30,0:37:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that incredible state
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.30,0:37:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,called the peace of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.30,0:37:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace of God, knowing that one is not
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.30,0:37:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,separated from the source of anything
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.30,0:37:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that one is connected with it
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.30,0:37:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that one is one with God.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.30,0:37:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,How does one then experience
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.34,0:37:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that which in body, mind and spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.91,0:37:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is called spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.91,0:38:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That subtle knowingness
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.91,0:38:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it can come from any one of life's
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.36,0:38:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,exigencies
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.36,0:38:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,from any one of life's tragedies
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.36,0:38:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,even from a minor disappointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.36,0:38:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,All of these things have within them
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.36,0:38:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the seed
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.68,0:38:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth is always present
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.68,0:38:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is the spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.68,0:38:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that which reveals itself
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.68,0:38:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.68,0:38:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth behind consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.68,0:38:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is always present
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.68,0:38:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore can be discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.68,0:38:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,at any moment
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.68,0:38:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in moments of high joy
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.68,0:38:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in moments of depression
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.68,0:38:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and so in Zen they say
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.68,0:38:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,heaven and hell are only a tenth of an inch apart
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.68,0:38:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,heaven and hell are only a tenth of an inch apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.68,0:38:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself of course
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.29,0:38:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and I share my own personal experience
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.29,0:38:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that I have experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.29,0:38:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and that I have witnessed the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.29,0:38:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of what I am talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.29,0:38:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,my own inner experience has been
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.29,0:38:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,a time of great depression
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.29,0:38:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,severe depression
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.29,0:38:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,agonizing depression
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.29,0:39:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,way down in the pits
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.29,0:39:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and from that state
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.29,0:39:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of absolute hopelessness
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.29,0:39:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,in which time stopped
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.29,0:39:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.29,0:39:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,went on for literally eons
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.29,0:39:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,because you know in a severe depression
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.29,0:39:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,our experience of time
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.29,0:39:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,is altered
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.29,0:39:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,each second seems like an eternity
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.29,0:39:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and so in this depressed state
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.35,0:39:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,time stopped and it went on for eons
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.35,0:39:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,eons and eons
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.35,0:39:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and in these eons
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.35,0:39:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,there was no hope
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.35,0:39:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,it's almost as if there was a sign
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.35,0:39:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact that sort of fantasy
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.35,0:39:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the sign that went over the top
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.35,0:39:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,it said all ye who enter here
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.35,0:39:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,give up all hope
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.35,0:39:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,like Dante's Inferno
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.15,0:39:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the hells
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.15,0:39:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and in that experience
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.15,0:39:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of that infinite suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.15,0:39:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and agony
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.15,0:39:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and self-hatred
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.15,0:39:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that total feeling of being separated from love
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.15,0:39:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and from God
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.15,0:39:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,came a great knowing
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.15,0:40:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly came a great knowing
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.15,0:40:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and from that pit
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.15,0:40:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,from those pits of agony
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.15,0:40:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly there was the awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.15,0:40:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of the infinite presence
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.15,0:40:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of eternal love
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.15,0:40:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the knowingness of truth
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.28,0:40:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so the kernel of that is
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.28,0:40:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,within any experience
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.28,0:40:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and once we've investigated
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.28,0:40:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,a thing and found out the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.28,0:40:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,for ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.28,0:40:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,this encourages us to continue to do this
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.31,0:40:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to never buy anything
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.31,0:40:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to be detrimental in our life again
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.31,0:40:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to use each one of these experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.31,0:40:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to search
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.31,0:40:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,right into the heart of the matter
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.31,0:40:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to look for what was the fear
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.31,0:40:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,what was the misunderstanding
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.31,0:40:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to do this
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.02,0:40:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,from a viewpoint of forgivingness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.02,0:40:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and so essential to this
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.02,0:40:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,self-healing is the willingness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.02,0:40:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to love ourself and forgive ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.02,0:40:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.02,0:40:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to look at our vulnerability
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.02,0:40:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and to call it our humanness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.02,0:40:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the capacity to love
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.02,0:40:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,our humanness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.02,0:41:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,for its weaknesses
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.02,0:41:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,for its errors
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.02,0:41:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,for its foibles
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.02,0:41:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to see that within this humanness
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.02,0:41:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,as mistaken as it might be
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.02,0:41:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,there was an intrinsic innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.82,0:41:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you see once we get off the anger
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.82,0:41:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,about our expectation
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.82,0:41:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and the fact that it didn't work out
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.82,0:41:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,because it can't in a changing world
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.82,0:41:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,this is a world
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.82,0:41:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,in which there is only one thing
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.82,0:41:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that is certain in the phenomenal
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.82,0:41:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,aspects of this world and its expression
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.82,0:41:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,as we experience it
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.82,0:41:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is that all things change
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.98,0:41:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,look at that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.98,0:41:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,all things change
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.98,0:41:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,all things change within human experience
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.98,0:41:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because human experience is
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.98,0:41:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that of change
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.01,0:41:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,if all things change
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.01,0:41:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and nothing remains the same
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.01,0:41:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,then to place the source of your happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.01,0:41:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,outside of yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.01,0:41:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,on that which changes
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.01,0:41:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,it's only a matter of time
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.01,0:41:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,before the depression ensues
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.04,0:41:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is that not correct
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.04,0:42:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and not appearing
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.04,0:42:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,coming and going and changing
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.04,0:42:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,then the vulnerability is ever present
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.62,0:42:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that simple mistake
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.62,0:42:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,which we all make
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.62,0:42:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,which is common to the whole human condition
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.62,0:42:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,which we are trying to look through today
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.65,0:42:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,arises out of something
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.65,0:42:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that is also the same in all of us
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.65,0:42:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and which can be rediscovered
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.65,0:42:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and rediscovered right in the pain
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.65,0:42:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of this experience
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.65,0:42:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is the intrinsic innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.65,0:42:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.65,0:42:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the intrinsic innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.65,0:42:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,of the inner self
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.87,0:42:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and this we can see
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.87,0:42:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in two different ways
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.87,0:42:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,one by reaching that state
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.87,0:42:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,of compassion
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.87,0:42:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and compassion ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.87,0:42:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,by reaching such a level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.87,0:42:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that we literally see into the hearts of others
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.87,0:42:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and we just see and know
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.87,0:42:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.26,0:42:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the other way is to
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.26,0:42:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,through introspection
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.26,0:42:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,look and see how this arose
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.96,0:42:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we notice in the child
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.96,0:42:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we notice the innocence of the child
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.96,0:43:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the young child we say
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.96,0:43:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is innocent
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.96,0:43:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and what do we mean by that
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.96,0:43:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we mean that he is trusting
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.96,0:43:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,he has faith in the integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.96,0:43:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of those around him
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.96,0:43:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it never dawns on the child's mind
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.96,0:43:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to doubt the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.96,0:43:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which is being told
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.96,0:43:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,so the young child loves the parents
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.96,0:43:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and those extensions of the parent
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.96,0:43:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,called teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.96,0:43:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,other family members
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.96,0:43:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,peers
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.18,0:43:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,playmates
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.18,0:43:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,television
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.18,0:43:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,commercials
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.18,0:43:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the child looks at a commercial
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.18,0:43:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,as though it's just as truthful
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.86,0:43:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,as its parent
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.86,0:43:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because of its trustingness
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.86,0:43:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because of its openness
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.86,0:43:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because of its lovingness
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.92,0:43:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because of its lack of paranoia
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.98,0:43:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you might say
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.98,0:43:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it's easily programmed
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.98,0:43:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore it begins to buy
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.98,0:43:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,out of its innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.98,0:43:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that which it hears
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.98,0:44:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,or that religious group
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.98,0:44:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.27,0:44:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and we don't like people that do this
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.27,0:44:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and we don't like people that do that
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.27,0:44:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and we don't like people that vote that way
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.56,0:44:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and the child's identification with those
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.56,0:44:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that he loves is family
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.56,0:44:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the programs start coming in
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.56,0:44:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so the innocence of the child now
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.56,0:44:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,gets programmed
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.56,0:44:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,why? because of its innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.56,0:44:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it's because of its innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.56,0:44:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that it buys such statements as
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.56,0:44:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,all of us Jeffersons are allergic
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.56,0:44:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,heart disease runs in our family
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.56,0:44:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,we all have a weight problem in our family
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.56,0:44:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and all these negative programs now
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.56,0:44:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,are bought out of the child's innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.56,0:44:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and so we might say
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.10,0:44:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the child is like the hardware of a computer
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.10,0:44:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the hardware of the computer
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.10,0:44:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,will play any software program
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.10,0:44:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that's put through it
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.71,0:44:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet the nature of the hardware
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.71,0:44:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the nature of that which is
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.71,0:44:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,truly the computer itself
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.71,0:44:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is unchanged
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.71,0:44:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what floppy disk we play
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.71,0:44:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what software
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.71,0:45:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,what programs we play through the computer
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.71,0:45:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,its intrinsic innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.71,0:45:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,its purity, its integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.71,0:45:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,has not been sullied
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.71,0:45:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it has not changed at all
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.71,0:45:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,we take out all the programs
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.71,0:45:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,which are erroneous
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.71,0:45:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and the hardware remains the same
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.74,0:45:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the same with consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.74,0:45:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that childlike consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.74,0:45:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,with its innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.74,0:45:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,with its purity of motive
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.74,0:45:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,with its capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.74,0:45:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to remain pure
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.74,0:45:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what the programs may be
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.74,0:45:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,remains essential and unchanged
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.74,0:45:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it is exactly what is listening
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.22,0:45:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to my voice right now
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.22,0:45:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it is that childlike consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.26,0:45:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in all its purity and innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.26,0:45:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that is what's listening
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.26,0:45:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to this voice right now
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.26,0:45:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,not the person
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.38,0:45:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,not the personality
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.38,0:45:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but that consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.38,0:45:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in all its pure and simple purity
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.38,0:45:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,even if that which is listening
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.25,0:45:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,says I don't believe a word of it
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.25,0:45:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,where does I don't believe
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.25,0:46:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,a word of it come from
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.25,0:46:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it comes from another word
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.25,0:46:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,another belief system
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.25,0:46:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that the child bought out of innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.25,0:46:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the father says don't trust anybody
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.25,0:46:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,or
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.50,0:46:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,some disappointing experience
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.50,0:46:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,sets up the program within the child's mind
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.50,0:46:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,don't trust anything you hear
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.08,0:46:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,so if you're saying to yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.08,0:46:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe anything he says
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.08,0:46:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you're saying that because out of the childlike innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.08,0:46:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you bought that program
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.08,0:46:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the way to be secure in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.08,0:46:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is don't believe anything you hear
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.08,0:46:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,or you'll be misled and led down the primrose path
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.21,0:46:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but the nature of the innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.21,0:46:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you bought that program remains the same
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.21,0:46:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is it not
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.21,0:46:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's not the mind right this moment
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.21,0:46:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to listen to the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.21,0:46:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,discern that which is the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.21,0:46:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,out of its hopefulness
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.21,0:46:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,out of its trustingness
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.21,0:46:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,hoping to hear that which will be helpful
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.21,0:46:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that which will nurture life
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.21,0:46:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that which will relieve suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.43,0:46:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and so you see that intrinsic innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.43,0:46:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,so that when you look within yourself now
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.43,0:46:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,into the self healing
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.43,0:47:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,into the understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.43,0:47:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of what was the program that was set up
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.43,0:47:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to re-own that innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.43,0:47:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in all spiritual work
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.43,0:47:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it is so crucial
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.56,0:47:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in all work in psychological research
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.56,0:47:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,within yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.56,0:47:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and introspection
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.56,0:47:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to always keep within your awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.56,0:47:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that whatever you bought
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.56,0:47:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you bought out of the beauty of what you are
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.56,0:47:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you bought it out of your own love
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.85,0:47:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and your own trustingness
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.85,0:47:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and you really bought it out of your own integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.85,0:47:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because you projected your own integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.85,0:47:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,onto the world
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.85,0:47:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and thought this is a place that you can trust and believe anything you hear
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.85,0:47:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because that is where you were coming from
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.85,0:47:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,until you got programmed
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.85,0:47:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that sometimes it is very useful to lie
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.85,0:47:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes it is useful
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.85,0:47:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to tell them the check is in the mail
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.85,0:47:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,we all know that one
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.91,0:47:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,we got programmed into the idea
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.91,0:47:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that the only way you can survive
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.91,0:47:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,as a body in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.91,0:47:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is you have to
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.91,0:47:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,tailor the truth a little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.91,0:47:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,create a business
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.91,0:48:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,business ethics
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.46,0:48:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but didn't we buy that out of our own innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.46,0:48:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we thought
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.46,0:48:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what they say
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.46,0:48:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you got to do in this world to survive
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.46,0:48:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,so I guess I got to do that
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.46,0:48:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course when you do that
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.46,0:48:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you pay the price
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.46,0:48:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,anytime we go below the line
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.46,0:48:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we pay the price
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.46,0:48:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and the price is we lose our power
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.46,0:48:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the loss of power within the world
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.62,0:48:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,so that's what the anger is about
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.62,0:48:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I lost my power
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.62,0:48:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of my happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.62,0:48:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,will never be returned to me
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.62,0:48:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,because it is outside of myself
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.62,0:48:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I projected it out there
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.62,0:48:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the healing of it then comes
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.62,0:48:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,from the willingness
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.62,0:48:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to look at the truth of this
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.71,0:48:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to say to myself
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.71,0:48:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,out of my innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.71,0:48:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,like other humans on this planet
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.81,0:48:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,like most of us in fact
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.81,0:48:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I brought a certain way of looking at life
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.81,0:48:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the source of happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.81,0:48:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is first of all
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.81,0:48:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,outside of myself
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.26,0:48:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,secondly it's always in the future
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.26,0:49:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the separation from the source of happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.26,0:49:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is not only in space
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.26,0:49:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's also in time
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.26,0:49:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,tomorrow or the next day
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.26,0:49:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,or next week
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.26,0:49:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,or the year after
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.26,0:49:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,or when I finally graduate
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.96,0:49:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,when I reach middle age
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.96,0:49:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,or when I get that big house
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.96,0:49:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,or when I get that Cadillac
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.96,0:49:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it's always in the future
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.96,0:49:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,so we're always separated
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.96,0:49:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,from the source of our happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.96,0:49:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and we never feel complete
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.96,0:49:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the realization that we are the source of our happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.96,0:49:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and that we can create it at any second
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.73,0:49:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,gives us a sense of completion
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.73,0:49:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the sense of completion then
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.79,0:49:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,so that it can be cut off at any second
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.79,0:49:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and feel complete
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.79,0:49:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,if we suddenly stop this talk
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.79,0:49:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,right now
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.79,0:49:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,it is complete right as of this moment
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.79,0:49:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I have with the best of my ability
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.79,0:49:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,said exactly what I wanted to say
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.79,0:49:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,not feeling I'm going to say it in a minute
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.79,0:49:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,not saying it's going to come tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.79,0:49:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but right now
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.79,0:49:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,being with the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.79,0:50:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of experiencing the joy
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.79,0:50:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of doing the best I can at this moment
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.79,0:50:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and so
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.82,0:50:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the joyfulness then
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.82,0:50:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,accompanies the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.82,0:50:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.89,0:50:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,tomorrow about it
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.05,0:50:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the sense of completion then
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.05,0:50:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,whether someone enjoys the talk
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.05,0:50:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is immaterial
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.05,0:50:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that is frosting on the cake
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.05,0:50:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but it is not part and parcel
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.46,0:50:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,what one does in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.46,0:50:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,has to be accompanied by
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.46,0:50:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the sense of completion
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.46,0:50:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in the doing of it itself
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.46,0:50:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the payoff is not something
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.46,0:50:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,which is an aside
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.46,0:50:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,which is something as separate
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.46,0:50:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,from the doingness
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.46,0:50:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience of it right now
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.46,0:50:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the completion is with
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.46,0:50:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiencing right now
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.46,0:50:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,not something separate from it
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.88,0:50:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in that then one is aware
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.88,0:50:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of the lovingness of all experience
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.88,0:50:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that is the way one is
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.88,0:50:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,with the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.88,0:50:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the loving of life
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.88,0:50:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,then in all its expressions
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.88,0:51:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the loving of life in all its expressions
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.88,0:51:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,including its disappointments
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.88,0:51:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,its ups and downs
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.88,0:51:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the continual
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.88,0:51:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,process of making the mistake
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.88,0:51:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and learning from the mistake
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.55,0:51:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,so that is nothing but a mistake then
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.55,0:51:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you might say depression
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.55,0:51:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is nature's way of saying to us
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.55,0:51:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,God's way of saying to us
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.55,0:51:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,our own psychology's way of saying
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.55,0:51:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it to us however
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.55,0:51:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at it
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.55,0:51:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is okay with you
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.55,0:51:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it's our psychological way
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.55,0:51:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,our biologic way
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.55,0:51:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,our spiritual way
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.55,0:51:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it's our body our mind and our spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.55,0:51:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,saying look what's out
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.55,0:51:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,there needs to be fixed
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.55,0:51:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,please understand me
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.55,0:51:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,out of your compassion heal
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.55,0:51:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,heal me heal all of us
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.84,0:51:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,which leads to the depression
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.84,0:51:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is this inner sense of separation
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.84,0:51:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.19,0:51:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I will not be complete and whole
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.19,0:51:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,unless I become united with something
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.19,0:51:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,out there
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.29,0:52:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,this brings up the difference
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.29,0:52:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,in the precipitating event
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.29,0:52:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that leads to suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.29,0:52:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,or depression
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.29,0:52:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,very often between men and women
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.29,0:52:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,men experience the presence of God
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.29,0:52:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,within them or the connection to God
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.29,0:52:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and very often in the form of power
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.29,0:52:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we remember that the three
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.29,0:52:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,classical attributes
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.29,0:52:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of God are omnipresence
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.29,0:52:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,omniscience omnipotence
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.29,0:52:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,so that God is often
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.29,0:52:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,experienced in the unconscious
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.29,0:52:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of men as connection
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.29,0:52:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,with power so that power
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.29,0:52:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes that
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.29,0:52:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,which they seek and therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.64,0:52:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the precipitating event
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.64,0:52:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,very often in men
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.64,0:52:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,leads to the depression
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.64,0:52:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,was feeling separated
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.64,0:52:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,from the source of one's power
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.64,0:52:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in this case the power has been put out
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.64,0:52:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,into the world so it would be
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.64,0:52:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the loss of a title
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.64,0:52:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,loss of a position loss of a business
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.64,0:52:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,loss of the status
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.64,0:52:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,symbols that signify that power
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.64,0:53:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and so that sense of
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.18,0:53:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,separation that vulnerability
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.18,0:53:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,because it has not been really healed
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.18,0:53:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,remains there
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.18,0:53:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore money position and power
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.18,0:53:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,become their traditional goals
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.18,0:53:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of men
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.57,0:53:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,women experience in the unconscious
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.57,0:53:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,their connection with God
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.57,0:53:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,more in the form of love
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.57,0:53:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,so that relationships are all important
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.57,0:53:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and the experience of love
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.57,0:53:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,through the relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.57,0:53:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,we remember the example
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.57,0:53:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of the old woman who sat in the rocking chair
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.57,0:53:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,rocking back and forth staring hopelessly
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.57,0:53:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,out the window
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.57,0:53:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it was because of feeling cut off
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.57,0:53:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,from a relationship and she experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.57,0:53:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that lovingness
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.57,0:53:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,coming through that relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.57,0:53:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and so the interruption of the relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.57,0:53:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,then was the precipitating factor
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.57,0:53:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and so we see that the basic
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.57,0:53:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,problem is still the same
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.57,0:53:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just that it takes different form
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.57,0:53:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,different expression
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.57,0:53:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,between the two sexes
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.57,0:53:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,depression leads us into
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.57,0:53:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,something we mentioned in the beginning of the film
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.57,0:54:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole subject of suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.57,0:54:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,when we look at suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.63,0:54:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll see that
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.63,0:54:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,what is desired is not
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.63,0:54:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,really death of the body
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.63,0:54:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,what is desired is relief
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.63,0:54:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,from suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.70,0:54:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the realization that that is
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.70,0:54:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,what is sought
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.70,0:54:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,relief from suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.70,0:54:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,see the body did not create the dilemma
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.70,0:54:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the body cannot experience the dilemma
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.70,0:54:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore the idea
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.70,0:54:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that if I get rid of the body
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.70,0:54:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I will get rid of the source
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.70,0:54:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is fallacious
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.70,0:54:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the body neither created it
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.70,0:54:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,nor did it experience it
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.70,0:54:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole problem is going on within consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.70,0:54:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore the solution is within consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.70,0:54:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to look at
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.70,0:54:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the nature of consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.70,0:54:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and see that that is where it arose
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.70,0:54:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is where it is being experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.70,0:54:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore that is
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.70,0:54:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,where it has to be solved
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.92,0:54:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the solution is to realize
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.92,0:54:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that what is desired is the relief
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.92,0:54:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,from suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.53,0:54:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.53,0:55:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,which identifies itself with the body
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.53,0:55:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and thinks I am a body
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.53,0:55:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,then the loss of the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.53,0:55:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of life due to the fact that
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.53,0:55:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the person is dispirited
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.53,0:55:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,leads to a decrease
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.53,0:55:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.53,0:55:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and we have the forms
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.53,0:55:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the many forms of passive suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.53,0:55:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I would say that
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.53,0:55:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the majority of deaths in the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.53,0:55:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world in fact
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.53,0:55:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,are really forms of passive suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.53,0:55:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the loss of that sense of aliveness
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.53,0:55:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that excitement
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.53,0:55:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and commitment to life
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.53,0:55:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and the passive suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.53,0:55:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,then takes many forms
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.53,0:55:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,statistically it shows up
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.53,0:55:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,as the automobile accident
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.53,0:55:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,what is passive suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.53,0:55:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,really failure to get out of the way
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.53,0:55:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of the bus isn't it
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.53,0:55:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,for some reason we just didn't care enough
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.53,0:55:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to take the precautions
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.53,0:55:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we didn't care enough
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.53,0:55:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to love our life
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.53,0:55:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we didn't value it enough
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.53,0:55:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to care for ourself to preserve it
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.53,0:55:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and so passive suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.53,0:56:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,takes the form of the person
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.53,0:56:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,who ignores their physical disease
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.53,0:56:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the diabetic who just
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.53,0:56:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't care to stay on
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.53,0:56:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the diet
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.53,0:56:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't care to take the insulin
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.10,0:56:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly goes into
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.10,0:56:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,insulin reactions and overdoses
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.10,0:56:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and diabetic coma
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.10,0:56:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,3, 4, 5 times in the hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.10,0:56:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,in diabetic coma until they leave
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.10,0:56:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in the addictions
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.26,0:56:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,we see that in the form of the overdose
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.26,0:56:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,traditionally the overdose
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.26,0:56:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the person who is taking
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.26,0:56:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple drugs for 20 years
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.26,0:56:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and then dies of an overdose
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.26,0:56:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,how could that be a miscalculation
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.26,0:56:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,there are experts on psychopharmacology
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.26,0:56:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,they've dosed themselves thousands
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.26,0:56:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and thousands of times
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.39,0:56:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it's called an accident
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.39,0:56:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no such thing as an accident
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.13,0:56:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the automobile accident
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.13,0:56:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,where the person was just careless
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.13,0:56:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,what we really see is a loss
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.13,0:56:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of desire to live
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.13,0:56:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is that not so
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.13,0:56:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the failure to heed health advice
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.13,0:57:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the failure to take care of one's health
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.13,0:57:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the failure to take care of one's assets
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.13,0:57:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,all indicating a loss
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.13,0:57:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of that energy
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.13,0:57:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that sense of aliveness
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.13,0:57:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,coming from deflated
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.13,0:57:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,first entrapped
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.13,0:57:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,deflated then dispirited
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.13,0:57:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,then the loss of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.13,0:57:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and then unconsciously
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.13,0:57:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,seeking a way out
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.13,0:57:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,so that one doesn't have to feel guilty
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.13,0:57:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,one doesn't have to feel guilty
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.13,0:57:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that they died of diabetic coma
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.13,0:57:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,one didn't bother to alter one's lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.13,0:57:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to prevent that coronary heart attack
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.13,0:57:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,if we realize
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.13,0:57:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that what we want
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.13,0:57:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is the relief of suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.13,0:57:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,then the relief of suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.13,0:57:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,comes about through an understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.13,0:57:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of the nature of consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.13,0:57:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,through the processes
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.13,0:57:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have described in this talk
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.13,0:57:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.13,0:57:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to experience out
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.13,0:57:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and it can be experienced out
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.13,0:57:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,all the symptoms
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.13,0:57:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that are being experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.13,0:57:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the looking at one's life
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.13,0:58:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and using a technique
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.13,0:58:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I call the worst scenario
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.13,0:58:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to sit down and look at your life
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.13,0:58:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and say
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.13,0:58:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the worst possible outcome
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.13,0:58:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.13,0:58:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that comes up with that
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.13,0:58:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and so resisting that feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.13,0:58:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to constantly cancel out
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.13,0:58:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the thoughts about it
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.13,0:58:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and instead handle the feeling directly
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.13,0:58:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and as we do that
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.13,0:58:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll notice that the symptoms
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.13,0:58:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,begin to abate
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.13,0:58:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,we come out of the depression
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.13,0:58:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,we're willing to look at the fear
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.13,0:58:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,we're willing to look at the way
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.13,0:58:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that this was set up
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.13,0:58:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,how we got set up
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.13,0:58:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,our anger about that
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.13,0:58:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,using the energy of the anger
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.13,0:58:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to want something better for ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.13,0:58:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,what it really means then
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.70,0:58:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is we have to recontextualize
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.70,0:58:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,our whole life
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.70,0:58:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to look at everything
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.70,0:58:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and say to ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.70,0:58:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,how can I hold this
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.70,0:58:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,so that it will have a value
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.70,0:58:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that is great enough
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.70,0:59:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that if it left my life
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.70,0:59:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I would still have that
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.70,0:59:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,which is worth living for
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.70,0:59:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to what about this
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.70,0:59:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,can I dedicate my life
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.70,0:59:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,what about my job
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.70,0:59:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,gives it meaning and significance
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.70,0:59:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,how can I see it in such a way
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.70,0:59:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that my value as a human being
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.70,0:59:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,will not be changed
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.70,0:59:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,if that should leave my life
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.70,0:59:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and so we have to look at our goals
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.70,0:59:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and our motives
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.70,0:59:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,what are we willing to dedicate
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.70,0:59:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,our life to
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.70,0:59:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,what does have significant meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.70,0:59:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,service to others
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.70,0:59:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,even if we lost all capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.70,0:59:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to serve our own life
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.70,0:59:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the meaning then
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.70,0:59:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,of being of service to others
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.70,0:59:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,we see people of course
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.70,0:59:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,have all kinds of disfigurations
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.70,0:59:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of losses
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.70,0:59:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and they go on
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.70,0:59:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,somehow life still has meaning to them
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.70,0:59:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,what does that mean
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.70,0:59:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,does it mean we are weaker than they are
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.70,0:59:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that morally they are superior
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.70,0:59:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,no, it means that somehow
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.70,1:00:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,they have sensed
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.70,1:00:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,some greater meaning in their life
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.70,1:00:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,they had to let go of a lesser meaning
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.70,1:00:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and find a greater meaning
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.70,1:00:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,so that is what depression means to us
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.70,1:00:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,it means that we settled
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.70,1:00:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,for a smaller meaning
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.70,1:00:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,less than the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.70,1:00:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to re-examine
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.70,1:00:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and see what was the true meaning
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.70,1:00:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,of that in our life
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.70,1:00:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,what about our life makes it worthwhile
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.70,1:00:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,even without that
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.70,1:00:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,direction by asking ourselves
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.70,1:00:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,a very simple question
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.70,1:00:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,we can do this as we go about
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.70,1:00:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,our daily life
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.70,1:00:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,growing in consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.31,1:00:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,is something that we do
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.31,1:00:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,as we go about our everyday business
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.31,1:00:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and we ask ourselves
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.31,1:00:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the question
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.86,1:00:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't live if I didn't have blank
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.86,1:00:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,life wouldn't be worth living
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.43,1:00:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,unless
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.43,1:00:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we fill in
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.78,1:00:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,what in our own mind
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.82,1:00:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,we have put in that blank space
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.82,1:00:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,where is our vulnerabilities
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.82,1:01:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,our vulnerabilities
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.82,1:01:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,are where we think
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.82,1:01:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we couldn't live without that
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.10,1:01:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,what if we put our survival on
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.10,1:01:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,so the whole technique then
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.10,1:01:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is to first find out
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.10,1:01:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,where the areas of vulnerability lie
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.26,1:01:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,sit down and picture
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.26,1:01:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we go about
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.55,1:01:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the process of
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.55,1:01:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,letting go, resisting
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.55,1:01:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,all the feelings that come up
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.55,1:01:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask your own inner consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.55,1:01:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,ask your own unconscious
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.74,1:01:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,ask the God within you
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.80,1:01:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,ask your super consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.80,1:01:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,however it is
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.80,1:01:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,ask your intuition
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.80,1:01:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,however you hold that inner questioning
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.80,1:01:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and you begin an inner questioning search
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.99,1:01:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,all of us have to do that
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.99,1:01:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the meaning of our life
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.99,1:01:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,what is it's significance
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.99,1:01:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is worth living for? What do we value that is greater than that which is limited and temporary?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.03,1:02:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,By removing all these things one by one, we find that that who we are is growing in stature.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.79,1:02:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We're no longer so vulnerable to external events because there's always two things going on.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.54,1:02:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There is the event out there as we see it in ordinary consciousness happening out there,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.98,1:02:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and then there is how we feel about that, and how we feel about it depends on our attitudes.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.30,1:02:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We can decide how we want to be with that. See, that who we are then and what its relationship
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.22,1:02:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is to that event, see? So I am one thing and the event is something else, and I have power over
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.86,1:02:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,how I want to hold that, how I want to value that relationship, how I want to picture it,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.50,1:02:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and whether I'm willing to give it the power over my life. Am I willing to give money enough power
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.90,1:03:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,over my life, that if I lose it, I no longer desire to live? Am I willing to give a relationship that
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.93,1:03:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,power over my life? Am I willing to give possessions, titles, degrees, cars? Think of all
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.38,1:03:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the things that people put and value greater than their own life and you see the enormous vulnerability.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.34,1:03:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's high up there within the most important causes of death,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.28,1:03:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and especially so in adolescence.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.88,1:03:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So what does it say about the values, then, that we're teaching our adolescents?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.94,1:03:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the transitory things that we're telling them to base their life on?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.46,1:03:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to reevaluate for ourself what is the importance,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.62,1:03:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the meaning of our life,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.52,1:03:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,what do we hold of sufficient value that it will preserve us
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.48,1:03:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in the face of any kind of a loss.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.99,1:04:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of this inner understanding, then, comes a reevaluation of that relationship
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.81,1:04:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,between body, mind, and spirit.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.87,1:04:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it is mind, then, that is setting our goals and our purposes.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.91,1:04:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If we begin to question our values, reevaluate our position with them,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.39,1:04:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,whether we like it or not,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.57,1:04:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,whether we like the term or not,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.21,1:04:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,we're really doing that which is called spiritual work.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.21,1:04:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What is spirit?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.45,1:04:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, that energy of life itself?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.33,1:04:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, we have a decision about its form.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.17,1:04:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We can decide what to give meaning to, what to give value to.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.05,1:04:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Within that energy field called consciousness, then, we have great freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.15,1:04:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We have great freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.43,1:04:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It is up to our own inner choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.55,1:04:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,By seeing that, by merely seeing,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.81,1:04:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have the choice of what we want to give value to,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.75,1:04:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,we reown our power.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.65,1:04:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We move up on the chart.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.09,1:04:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We move up from victim to source.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.49,1:05:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin to accept back our own power, which we have given to the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.55,1:05:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,With that comes an inner state of serenity.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.01,1:05:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,An inner state of serenity that I am experiencing the value of my existence,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.25,1:05:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that I need no proof.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.19,1:05:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The world doesn't have to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.69,1:05:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need to bring home the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.53,1:05:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need to bring home any trophies to give it value,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.33,1:05:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because I see its value within myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.59,1:05:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I see and I treasure and I hold sacred the value of life itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.29,1:05:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,No trophies are needed.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.73,1:05:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I accept that which is given me with thanks.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.97,1:05:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,With gratitude, I hold the essence of that which I am,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.50,1:05:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,without asking that the world give me back anything that I've demanded of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.39,1:05:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,In doing that,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.91,1:05:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,we move into an invulnerable position.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.91,1:05:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We're no longer prone to these disappointments, the anger, the rage,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.23,1:05:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,turning against ourself and the thoughts of suicide,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.73,1:06:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that hopeless, fallacious idea that by killing the body,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.57,1:06:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we will kill the source of our suffering.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.35,1:06:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,By owning that we ourselves are the source of our suffering,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.53,1:06:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,we transcend it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.93,1:06:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,By transcending it, we bring about that inner healing,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.13,1:06:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the purpose of today's talk.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.91,1:06:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
